caption: My wife and I have been coming to this location for years. The other night we ordered a few sandwiches through Door Dash. In addition to my two sandwiches we grabbed a couple of bags of the BBQ crunchy awesome chips they have--the guy who took my order and delivered in curbside was amazing as well!  It was AMAZING, just like old times.

Stumbled miserably into Potbelly's immediately following a root canal in search of liquid sustenance, my heart set on chicken noodle soup and a coffee shake. To my dismay, the menu listed seemingly every option other than the coveted chicken noodle. As politely as I could, trying to avoid drooling from my temporarily paralyzed face, I asked a team member if they had any other soups available, and the response was that, unfortunately, they did not. After thanking her and turning to walk out in search of my soup - my sole reason to go on in face of diminishing Novocain and a gutted tooth throbbing with pain - LeLe stated that she would be happy to get me chicken noodle soup, unaware of the painful start to my day, and the half-smile it would bring to my face. While it may sound like a small act of kindness, in the right moment, even the smallest acts can really turn a day around and bring warmth to the heart of a victim of dental work! Thank you, LeLe!

Potbelly is a constantly reliable sandwich chain, an ever-present reminder that just because a restaurant is a chain it doesn't have to be bad. Potbelly has quick, cheap, and high-quality food, and the decor is always pleasant. Lines move quickly and Potbelly is a great place to get a sandwich or a salad almost always.

Great subs... the big roast beef will forever be a favorite. Reasonably price and the size satisfy my hunger. The ambiance of the place feel very retro and not like a standard chain. Despite being a chain it maintains a home-y feel,

The best oatmeal chocolate chip cookies and great milkshakes and I also love the Wreck salad.  This Potbelly's has great service and a great atmosphere.  Try the pizza sub or their chicken salad.  Both great! Very reasonably priced, fresh and filling.

Potbelly's is consistently good and this location does a good job cranking people through quickly.  The sandwiches are well made and the ingredients are fresh.  It's inexpensive and fast.
